nd:transparent;opacity:0.2"></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1675759363835" class="gf_row gf_row-fluid gf_row-no-padding" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1675759363835" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1675759363907" data-id="1675759363907"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675759985184" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1675759985184"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h1 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Legami</h1></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1680594068361" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1680594068361"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1680594068342" data-id="1680594068342"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675760058653" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675760058653"><div class="elm text-edit gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><font color="#000000">Legami is a creative workshop in Italy, making beautiful stationery and lifestyle goods, inspired by travel and curiosity. Their products are set apart by the thought that's gone into every detail, and the care put into the quality of the materials and workmanship.</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><font color="#000000"><br></font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><font color="#000000">They produce a lot of novelty stationery. We love stationery. I mean, we would, really, we’re <i>Cult Pens</i>, of course we do. But we’ve often found quite limited appeal in novelty stationery. You know the stuff, the pens with cute animals on the end, multicolour pens with the end shaped like a unicorn. The problem is, these are usually novelty items first, and stationery second. A plastic bear that the company has stuck to the end of a bad pen. Which is why we love Legami so much. They’re a stationery company at heart, but they make pens with cute bears on the end, and rainbow multipens shaped like unicorns. But it’s all <i>good quality</i>.</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><font color="#000000"><br></font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 14px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"><font color="#000000">And that makes all the difference - we love cute things, and when cute stationery is done well, it’s joyful.</font></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679581028534" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679581028534" data-layout-lg="3+3+3+3" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="3+3+3+3" data-layout-sm="6+6+6+6" data-layout-xs="6+6+6+6"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-3 gf_col-md-3 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-6" id="c-1679580858851" data-id="1679580858851"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679580874912" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1679580874912" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div 